<h1 id="01-ixio">01. <a href="http://ix.io/">ix.io</a></h1>
<p>Your code is shared via the command line, for example:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"><span class="c"># Sharing a file and getting the link</span>
<span class="nb">cat </span>mycode.sh | curl <span class="nt">-F</span> <span class="s1">'f:1=&lt;-'</span> ix.io</code></pre></figure>

<p>The output will inform you of the link you can use to share. If you want more ease, create a Shell function for this or use their client available on the same page, in addition to other options, such as saving codes and links when running the command.</p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/code/ix.png" alt="ix.io" /></p>

<p>Generated code link: <a href="http://ix.io/2eZc">http://ix.io/2eZc</a></p>

<!-- LISTA MIN -->
<script async="" src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>

<p><ins class="adsbygoogle" style="display:inline-block;width:730px;height:95px" data-ad-client="ca-pub-2838251107855362" data-ad-slot="5351066970"></ins>
<script>
(adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});
</script></p>

