<h1 id="09-ubuntu-pastebin">09. <a href="https://paste.ubuntu.com/">Ubuntu PasteBin</a></h1>
<p>It goes without saying that it is from <a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/generate-automatic-motivational-phrases-in-terminal/">distribution</a> <a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/the-fuck-the-command-that-corrects-incorrectly-typed-commands/">Linux</a> <a href="https://en.terminalroot.com.br/ubuntu-christian-an-ubuntu-linux-for-christians/">Ubuntu</a> with a clean and professional interface:
<img src="/assets/img/code/ubuntu-snippet-1.jpg" alt="Ubuntu PasteBin paste" />
<img src="/assets/img/code/ubuntu-snippet-2.jpg" alt="Ubuntu PasteBin code" /></p>

<p>Generated code link: <a href="https://paste.ubuntu.com/p/bwqY6XHpqm/">https://paste.ubuntu.com/p/bwqY6XHpqm/</a></p>

<h1 id="10-0x0st">10. <a href="http://0x0.st/">0x0.st</a></h1>
<p><img src="/assets/img/code/0x0.jpg" alt="0x0.st" />
This is complete, it is not just a code snippet, but a file sharing, url and everything you want within the limit of 512MB.</p>

<p>It is an alternative to <a href="https://transfer.sh/">transfer.sh</a>. Example of use:</p>

<figure class="highlight"><pre><code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash">curl <span class="nt">-F</span><span class="s1">'file=@mycode.sh '</span>http://0x0.st</code></pre></figure>

<hr />

<p>There is no shortage of options, feel free to choose in this alternative world! üòÄÔ∏è One that I would definitely not recommend would be <del>PasteBin.com</del>, this one generates <a href="https://terminalroot.com.br/2014/09/resolvendo-bad-interpreter-no-bash. html">‚Äòbad interpreter‚Äô</a> in your code, if you download and use it on Linux.</p>

